$$$f\left( x \right) = \left\{ {\matrix{
   {2x,} &amp; {\left| x \right| \le 1}  \cr 
   {{x^2} + ax + b,} &amp; {\left| x \right| &gt; 1}  \cr 

 } } \right\}$$$
<p>Find the area of the region in the third quadrant bounded by the curves $$x =  - 2{y^2}$$ and $$y=f(x)$$ lying on the left of the line $$8x+1=0.$$</p>

If  $$\left[ {\matrix{
   {4{a^2}} &amp; {4a} &amp; 1  \cr 
   {4{b^2}} &amp; {4b} &amp; 1  \cr 
   {4{c^2}} &amp; {4c} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]\left[ {\matrix{
   {f\left( { - 1} \right)}  \cr 
   {f\left( 1 \right)}  \cr 
   {f\left( 2 \right)}  \cr 

 } } \right] = \left[ {\matrix{
   {3{a^2} + 3a}  \cr 
   {3{b^2} + 3b}  \cr 
   {3{c^2} + 3c}  \cr 

 } } \right],\,\,f\left( x \right)$$ is a quadratic 
<br>function and its maximum value occurs at a point $$V$$. $$A$$ is a point of intersection of $$y=f(x)$$ with $$x$$-axis and point $$B$$ is such that chord $$AB$$ subtends a right angle at  $$V$$. Find the area enclosed by $$f(x)$$ and chord $$AB$$.

